org.apache.oodt.cas.metadata

Class Metadata

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.oodt.cas.metadata.Metadata
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    SerializableMetadata, VelocityMetadata

    public class Metadata
extends Object
    Metadata is a Map of String keys mapped to Object values. So, each key can map to potentially many values, but also can map to null, or to a single value.
    Version:
    $Revision$
    Author:
    mattmann, bfoster

        @Deprecated
public void addMetadata(Map<String,Object> metadata,
                                    boolean replace)
        Deprecated. 
        Takes a Map of String keys and Object values. Values of type List must be a List of Strings; all other values will have its toString() method invoked.
        Parameters:
        metadata - Map based metadata to add
        replace - If true, existing keys will be replaced, other values will be combined.
